Juan Imhoff (L) made the last of his 33 Argentina appearances last July PARIS - Argentina winger Juan Imhoff has signed a new deal with Racing 92, the French Top 14 club announced on Wednesday despite reports claiming he would leave at the end of the season.  He chose against featuring for the Pumas at the 2019 Rugby World Cup due to his club commitments. Thirteen other players including France hooker Camille Chat, Les Bleus flanker Ibrahim Diallo and Namibia lock Anton Bresler have also extended their stays a well as defence coach Dimitri Szarzewski. On Sunday, the three-time European Champions Cup runners-up host Sale Sharks in the competition's quarter-finals.